# Habit Loop Canvas Restructuring

Restructure the web app so the main canvas is a **4-part Habit Loop** (жҸҗзӨәвҶ’жёҙжңӣвҶ’еӣһжҮүвҶ’зҚҺиіһ) with directed graph editing (nodes + edges). Move the old tree canvas to `old.html`. Simplify the вҳ° menu and add a file automation settings view.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The **old tree canvas and all its functionality** will be fully preserved in `old.html`. The new [index.html](file:///c:/Users/ba/OneDrive/%E6%A1%8C%E9%9D%A2/exam/docs/index.html) replaces `view-tree` with the habit loop canvas but **keeps** `view-welcome`, `view-editor`, and all shared infrastructure (TOS, Auth, Drive sync, toasts, modals, conflict resolution, footer).

> [!WARNING]
> The `humanTree` data model changes. The new canvas uses a flat `{ nodes: [], edges: [] }` structure instead of the tree hierarchy. **Existing serialized tree data will NOT automatically migrate** вҖ” the old format is only usable in `old.html`.

## Proposed Changes

### Component 1: Preserve Old Canvas

#### [NEW] [old.html](file:///c:/Users/ba/OneDrive/жЎҢйқў/exam/docs/old.html)
- Full copy of current [index.html](file:///c:/Users/ba/OneDrive/%E6%A1%8C%E9%9D%A2/exam/docs/index.html) (all 3736 lines) вҖ” preserving tree canvas, editor, auth, everything
- Zero modifications to the copied content

