### Component 2: New Habit Loop Canvas

#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///c:/Users/ba/OneDrive/жЎҢйқў/exam/docs/index.html)

**CSS additions (~200 lines):**
- `.habit-canvas-container` вҖ” full-viewport canvas with grid background (reuses existing infinite canvas pattern)
- `.habit-column` вҖ” 4 vertical columns for Cue/Craving/Response/Reward, each with header + color accent
- `.habit-node` вҖ” draggable node boxes with stage-colored borders
- `.habit-node-add` вҖ” dashed add-node buttons per column
- `.habit-edge-svg` вҖ” SVG overlay layer for arrow rendering
- `.habit-column-header` вҖ” stage label + emoji at top of each column

**HTML changes:**
- Replace `view-tree` inner content: remove `tree-canvas-container`, `tree-zoom-layer`, `tree-render-area`, `canvas-ui-layer`
- New content: 4-column layout with SVG overlay, column headers, node add buttons
- Keep `auth-bar` and `more-options-wrapper` in `view-tree`

**JS changes:**
- New data model:
  ```js
  let habitGraph = { nodes: [], edges: [] };
  // Node: { id, text, stage: "cue"|"craving"|"response"|"reward", x, y }
  // Edge: { id, from: nodeId, to: nodeId }
  ```
- `renderHabitCanvas()` вҖ” renders nodes into columns, draws SVG arrows
- `addHabitNode(stage, text)` вҖ” adds node to specified stage
- `startEdgeDrag(nodeId)` / `endEdgeDrag(nodeId)` вҖ” creates edge between two nodes
- `deleteHabitNode(nodeId)` вҖ” removes node and connected edges
- `deleteHabitEdge(edgeId)` вҖ” removes an edge
- Canvas panning/zooming reused from existing code (same `tree-canvas-container` approach)
- [serializeTreeForSync()](file:///c:/Users/ba/OneDrive/%E6%A1%8C%E9%9D%A2/exam/docs/index.html#3227-3251) updated to serialize `habitGraph` instead of `humanTree`
- [restoreTreeFromSerialized()](file:///c:/Users/ba/OneDrive/%E6%A1%8C%E9%9D%A2/exam/docs/index.html#2735-2768) updated to handle new format

